        "ScenePath": "assembly:/_PRO/Scenes/Missions/Paris/_scene_paris.entity",
        "TileImage": "$($repository c400e1cd-500f-4f20-a6d3-efe8d31eb288).Image",
        "Description": "Napoléon Bonaparte was a french military leader in the 19th century. He made many campaigns and he extended the French empire across Europe.\rBut after many defeats, people claimed his death and he was exiled on Saint Helena, and he died.\rOr did he? He actually engaged himself in the piracy and survived. And after 200 years, he&apos;s back to punish heirs of people who exiled him. \r\rWear the Buccaneer suit for more realism.\r\rDifficulty: 4/5",
